CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 12, 1962, pg. A23 reads: "Hold Teen Talk - The Sequoires Tri Hi-Y Club of Centre Avenue branch YMCA held a "Teen Talk" program. This program offered youth the opportunity to come to grips with some of the more controversial subjects involving the youth of today.  Left to right are: Joyce Lesense, Joyce Lane, Florazine Strothers, Susan Carroll, Jeanette Finch, Yvonne Banks, Delphine Freeman, Patsy Austin, Diane Dickson, Mrs. Lovette, club adviser; Patricia Lanon, Carol Olston, Andrea Williams, and Shelia Bailey."
TitMainTitle: Fourteen members of the Sequoires Tri Hi-Y Club, left to right; Joyce Lesense, Joyce Lane, Florazine Strothers, Susan Carroll, Jeanette Finch, Yvonne Banks, Delphine Freeman, Patsy Austin, Diane Dickson, Mrs. Lovette, club adviser; Patricia Lanon, Carol Olston, Andrea Williams, and Shelia Bailey, gathered in semi-circle in classroom of Centre Avenue YMCA
